"v.嘲笑；狼吞虎咽；n.嘲笑，笑柄 【英】 v. 嘲笑(to show contempt by derisive acts or language);v. 狼吞虎咽(to eat greedily) 【例】 the scoffs of one's fellow(同伴的嗤笑) v. /n. 嘲笑 【记】读: 死搞妇, 死也要搞定一个妇女的人值得嘲笑. 【类】pontificate: pompous = scoff: derisive[contempt] = drawl: slow = bluster: loud = prate: aimless = thankful: gratitude武断: 高傲的 = 嘲笑: 嘲笑的 = 慢慢说: 慢的 = 怒号: 大声的 = 闲聊: 无目的的 = 感谢的: 感激 【记】音：抠腹，抠肚子会使人笑；s 死命地cough 咳嗽，因为嘲笑，笑得太厉害，或者吃得太猛造成； scoff (v.)  mid-14c., ""jest, make light of something;"" mid-15c., ""make fun of, mock,"" from the noun meaning ""contemptuous ridicule"" (c.1300), from a Scandinavian source such as Old Norse skaup, skop ""mockery, ridicule,"" Middle Danish skof ""jest, mockery;"" perhaps from Proto-Germanic *skub-, *skuf- (cognates: Old English scop ""poet,"" Old High German scoph ""fiction, sport, jest, derision""), from PIE *skeubh- ""to shove"" (see shove (v.))."
